00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,459
Good evening. Welcome to Market Pulse tonight. I'm your anchor and today we bring you a major

00:00:05,459 --> 00:00:09,539
development rippling across India's economy. The Indian rupee has plunged past the historic

00:00:09,539 --> 00:00:15,050
minute per US dollar mark. This plunge isn't just a number. It signals turbulence for businesses,

00:00:15,050 --> 00:00:19,359
for consumers, for ordinary citizens. So let's dive into what this means, why it happened and

00:00:19,359 --> 00:00:24,420
what could be coming next. First, the facts. On Wednesday and Thursday, December 2025,

00:00:24,420 --> 00:00:29,750
the rupee breached the psychological barrier of 90 per US dollar for the first time ever.

00:00:29,750 --> 00:00:37,670
At one point, it touched an intraday low of 90.33 and subsequent session saw it slide further, reaching around 90.41 and 90.43.

00:00:37,670 --> 00:00:39,369
Why, some reports are here.

00:00:39,369 --> 00:00:45,629
Oh, the rupee closed at about 90.19 per dollar, a dramatic fall that reflects deepening pressure on the currency.

00:00:45,629 --> 00:00:46,939
That's a part of me.

00:00:46,939 --> 00:00:48,310
The slide hasn't come overnight, though.

00:00:48,310 --> 00:00:48,769
Whoa!

00:00:48,769 --> 00:00:50,820
This depreciation is part of a broader trend.

00:00:50,820 --> 00:00:57,340
Over 2025, the rupee has slipped roughly 5% against the US dollar, making it one of Asia's worst-performing currencies this year.

00:00:57,340 --> 00:00:58,299
Contextualizing.

00:00:58,299 --> 00:01:01,719
not long ago, many wouldn't have imagined a rupee to dollar rate crossing 90.

00:01:01,719 --> 00:01:02,780
..

00:01:02,780 --> 00:01:07,250
But for decades now, the rupee's value has eroded gradually, shaped by economic shifts,

00:01:07,250 --> 00:01:12,099
global pressures and internal challenges. So, what caused this steep fall? And this

00:01:12,099 --> 00:01:16,039
points to a handful of critical factors. First, foreign capital flight. In recent weeks,

00:01:16,039 --> 00:01:20,159
there's been a steady outflow of funds from Indian equities. Foreign portfolio investors,

00:01:20,159 --> 00:01:25,319
FBIs, have been pulling out, spooked by durable uncertainties, rising US yields,

00:01:25,319 --> 00:01:29,560
unchanging risk perceptions. Simultaneously domestic demand for

00:01:29,560 --> 00:01:34,140
dollars surged. Importers, especially in sectors like oil, metals, electronics are

00:01:34,140 --> 00:01:37,040
scrambling to secure dollars amid uncertainty, increasing demand pressure

00:01:37,040 --> 00:01:41,920
on USD and pushing INR down. Second, uncertainty over international trade and

00:01:41,920 --> 00:01:46,599
tariffs. The stalled trade negotiations between India and the US along with

00:01:46,599 --> 00:01:51,140
steep US along with steep US. Delifts and Indian goods have sapped confidence in

00:01:51,140 --> 00:01:54,840
India's export prospects. That weighs on foreign investment sentiment and by

00:01:54,840 --> 00:01:56,120
by extension on the rupee.

00:01:56,120 --> 00:02:00,959
As one market commentary puts it, exporters are delaying conversions, hoping for a weaker

00:02:00,959 --> 00:02:05,439
rupee, while importers waste to convert sooner, a dynamic that drives instability.

00:02:05,439 --> 00:02:09,410
Third, lack of aggressive intervention from the Reserve Bank of India RBI.

00:02:09,410 --> 00:02:13,719
While historically the RBI has stepped in to defend certain levels, this time its restraint,

00:02:13,719 --> 00:02:17,139
reportedly choosing selective smoothing of volatility rather than holding a firm line,

00:02:17,139 --> 00:02:19,400
has allowed market dynamics to drive the currency lower.

00:02:19,400 --> 00:02:23,379
And fourth, the cumulative effect of global macroeconomic shifts.

00:02:23,379 --> 00:02:29,349
Strong US oil demand, rising US interest rates, global risk-cost sentiment,

00:02:29,349 --> 00:02:32,259
which have made emerging market currencies like the rupee more vulnerable.

00:02:32,259 --> 00:02:36,579
So we have a perfect storm, capital outflows, import-driven demand for dollars,

00:02:36,579 --> 00:02:39,550
trade uncertainty and limited central bank cushioning.

00:02:39,550 --> 00:02:41,490
But what does this mean for Indians?

00:02:41,490 --> 00:02:43,329
From the common man to businesses.

00:02:43,329 --> 00:02:47,240
In practical terms, in practical terms, the impact could be wide and deep.

00:02:47,240 --> 00:02:51,759
For starters, imports are going to get costlier. Everything imported, fuel, electronics, critical

00:02:51,759 --> 00:02:56,110
raw materials, medical equipment, technology becomes more expensive as the rupee weakens.

00:02:56,110 --> 00:03:01,659
That cost often passes on to consumers. This in turn fuels inflation. As the cost of essential

00:03:01,659 --> 00:03:06,000
imports rises, the ripple effect can push up prices of goods and services from petrol to

00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:10,409
smartphones to consumer electronics to hospital equipment. Ordinary households may feel the pinch.

00:03:10,409 --> 00:03:15,060
For people planning foreign travel, overseas education or foreign denominated loans,

00:03:15,060 --> 00:03:18,599
loans, the pain is more immediate. Students studying abroad now face higher costs when

00:03:18,599 --> 00:03:22,879
converting rubies to dollars. Tuition, living expenses, EMIs and foreign currency loans

00:03:22,879 --> 00:03:28,949
all get more expensive. For businesses dependent on imported raw materials, manufacturing units,

00:03:28,949 --> 00:03:34,000
pharma companies, pharma companies, tech firms, the cost base may expand, potentially squeezing

00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:37,910
margins or forcing higher prices. For import heavy sectors like electronics or chemicals,

00:03:37,910 --> 00:03:41,759
this could spell trouble. On the fixed side, a weaker rupee could give a boost to exports

00:03:41,759 --> 00:03:45,379
exports and remittances. For export-oriented firms, particularly those in reference price

00:03:45,379 --> 00:03:50,259
industries like IT services, manufacturing for overseas clients, their revenues in dollars now

00:03:50,259 --> 00:03:55,879
convert to more rupees, which might improve profitability. Similarly, remittances from

00:03:55,879 --> 00:03:59,500
Indians working abroad may be more valuable, potentially increasing inflows and helping

00:03:59,500 --> 00:04:03,400
households dependent on dollars. But at this moment, the immediate sentiment is of concern

00:04:03,400 --> 00:04:08,639
and anxiety. Many ordinary citizens and small businesses may only see rising costs and shrinking

00:04:08,639 --> 00:04:12,139
shrinking value of savings. What about the bigger picture? The economy and the markets?

00:04:12,139 --> 00:04:17,100
For one, domestic equity markets have responded nervously. The foreign rupee typically dampens

00:04:17,100 --> 00:04:21,100
investor confidence. Foreign investors pull out, domestic investors grow cautious, and

00:04:21,100 --> 00:04:26,040
equities may slump under pressure. At the same time, macroeconomic fundamentals remain

00:04:26,040 --> 00:04:30,519
nuanced. Despite this currency weakness, some analysts assert that the rupee remains undervalued,

00:04:30,519 --> 00:04:35,779
suggesting the slide may be more about external pressure than domestic decay. Indeed, as both

00:04:35,779 --> 00:04:37,909
quote by officials, the economy still shows strength.

00:04:37,909 --> 00:04:39,990
But the gap between dollar demand and dollar supply,

00:04:39,990 --> 00:04:44,159
driven by trade dynamics and foreign flows, is what's tilting the balance.

00:04:44,159 --> 00:04:46,539
Looking ahead, what could come next?

00:04:46,539 --> 00:04:49,779
Many analysts caution that the slide may not stop at 90,

00:04:49,779 --> 00:04:52,939
with speculative trading already rising and hedging costs surging in forward markets.

00:04:52,939 --> 00:04:59,420
Some forecasts suggest the rupee could test 90.90.91.naughty.90.naught per dollar

00:04:59,420 --> 00:05:00,819
if current dynamics persist.

00:05:00,819 --> 00:05:05,899
The upcoming meetings of the Monetary Policy Committee, MPC, IMPC,

00:05:05,899 --> 00:05:08,560
of global interest rate decisions especially in the US,

00:05:08,560 --> 00:05:12,189
and progress or lack thereof in international trade negotiations,

00:05:12,189 --> 00:05:14,529
especially between India and the US,

00:05:14,529 --> 00:05:17,750
will likely play a big role in determining where the rupee goes from here.

00:05:17,750 --> 00:05:20,189
Hmm, for now, hmm.

00:05:20,189 --> 00:05:23,750
The mood among policymakers seems to be one of caution mixed with resolve,

00:05:23,750 --> 00:05:25,139
intervening selectively.

00:05:25,139 --> 00:05:26,240
Oh, oh.

00:05:26,240 --> 00:05:28,950
But allowing some degree of currency flexibility.

00:05:28,950 --> 00:05:30,620
Ha ha ha ha ha.

00:05:30,620 --> 00:05:34,669
So what should citizens, businesses and investors do now?

00:05:34,669 --> 00:05:41,079
Ordinary households be prepared for potential price hikes, especially for goods that rely heavily on imports.

00:05:41,079 --> 00:05:49,759
If you have any dollar denominated obligations, education abroad, travel, loans, re-evaluate plans or consider hedging now.

00:05:49,759 --> 00:05:50,839
..

00:05:50,839 --> 00:05:55,210
Poor businesses, especially import heavy ones, review supply chains, Laskari, Koo.

00:05:55,210 --> 00:05:59,220
Renegocie a contract if possible or look for alternative sourcing.

00:05:59,220 --> 00:06:00,800
Exporters may find opportunity,

00:06:00,800 --> 00:06:02,860
but they must also watch global demand

00:06:02,860 --> 00:06:04,610
and foreign exchange hedging costs.

00:06:04,610 --> 00:06:08,509
For investors, this may call for caution in equities,

00:06:08,509 --> 00:06:10,519
especially in sectors dependent on imports

00:06:10,519 --> 00:06:11,459
or foreign raw materials.

00:06:11,459 --> 00:06:12,880
..

00:06:12,880 --> 00:06:14,600
On the flip side, export-oriented firms

00:06:14,600 --> 00:06:15,980
or companies with dollar-earning businesses

00:06:15,980 --> 00:06:17,670
may gain a relative advantage.

00:06:17,670 --> 00:06:20,300
In short, a slide of the repeated 90 per dollar

00:06:20,300 --> 00:06:22,139
marks a critical inflection point,

00:06:22,139 --> 00:06:24,279
one that cool, reshape costs,

00:06:24,279 --> 00:06:26,019
business dynamics, savings,

00:06:26,019 --> 00:06:27,649
and economic sentiment across India.

00:06:27,649 --> 00:06:30,080
As always, the coming days and weeks will be crucial.

00:06:30,080 --> 00:06:31,230
Will the currency stabilize?

00:06:31,230 --> 00:06:34,529
Or will policy response from the RBIO government bring confidence back?

00:06:34,529 --> 00:06:37,970
Or will global headwinds continue to batter the rupee's value?

00:06:37,970 --> 00:06:39,879
For now, we stay on watch.

00:06:39,879 --> 00:06:40,300
.

